Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.00,0:00:05.00,DCMain,,0000,0000,0000,,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.96,0:00:04.48,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,The Red Woman was seriously scary!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.98,0:00:08.46,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,Though, I guess it wasn't the actual \NRed Woman who attacked us.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.46,0:00:09.71,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,I know.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.71,0:00:12.75,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Who knows what would have happened
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.75,0:00:14.36,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,if Inspector Yamato and Inspector \NMorofushi hadn't arrived?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.79,0:00:18.74,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,I think we could've easily \Nsubdued her without them.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.74,0:00:21.27,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,You {\i1}are{\i0} super strong.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.27,0:00:24.09,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Do you do anything besides martial arts?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.09,0:00:27.25,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,When I was little, I was \Nall about jeet kune do.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.67,0:00:33.93,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,I'd watch and copy the videos my oldest \Nbrother sent me until they wore out.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:33.93,0:00:36.64,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,There was a dojo in my neighborhood, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.64,0:00:41.35,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,I only dabbled in other sports \Nduring PE classes at school.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:41.67,0:00:44.97,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,But after I moved to \NAmerica in middle school,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.97,0:00:48.24,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,I sometimes played other \Nsports with my friends.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.24,0:00:51.36,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,There wasn't a dojo where I ended up, either.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:51.36,0:00:53.01,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:53.01,0:00:55.74,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,I used to watch a lot of \Nsports with my mom on TV.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:56.22,0:01:01.34,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,That's how I know Conan-kun's \Npretty good at football.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.34,0:01:02.75,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Th-Thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:03.14,0:01:06.04,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Is your mother still in America?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:06.37,0:01:07.28,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:07.28,0:01:11.55,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,Because of that, I've been living alone \Nin a hotel since I returned to Japan.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:11.92,0:01:17.26,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,I tried moving in with my middle brother \Nwho's been living in Japan this whole time,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:17.26,0:01:18.88,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,but he turned me down.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:18.88,0:01:20.80,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,You're living in a hotel?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:20.80,0:01:23.31,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,Are you sure you're not the \Ndaughter of some rich family?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:24.52,0:01:27.94,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,My dad's friend who's always \Nlooked after me is rich.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:28.41,0:01:30.71,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,He's not as rich as your family, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:32.30,0:01:35.54,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,I don't have any other \Nrelatives to depend on.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:35.54,0:01:39.95,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,Once I get older, I know \NI should pay him back.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:40.96,0:01:45.36,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,If she has two brothers and doesn't \Nknow any of her relatives,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.00,0:01:51.96,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,then who is that young girl I saw on \Nher phone who looks just like her?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.30,0:01:54.83,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, is that hotel around here?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.83,0:01:56.19,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,Y-Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.19,0:01:58.30,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,Do you mind if we stop by?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.30,0:02:01.66,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,I'd like to see where you live, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.66,0:02:03.95,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,Sure, I guess.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.95,0:02:07.10,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,I should e-mail my brother, then.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.10,0:02:10.60,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,I had actually promised to meet my brother.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.25,0:02:12.80,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Never mind, then.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.80,0:02:13.61,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,It's okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.33,0:02:20.61,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,I made my brother agree to meet me to\Ndiscuss the Red Woman case in person.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.29,0:02:31.01,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,The hidden lines on the palm are the fuse.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.01,0:02:32.92,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,The deduction catches fire \Non the line to the heart.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.92,0:02:34.81,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,A popular author is confined \Nto his room in a hotel.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.81,0:02:37.01,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,The romance novel becomes a mystery.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.01,0:02:40.34,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Always determining the one truth with the \Nbody of a child and the mind of an adult,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.35,0:02:42.51,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,his name is Detective Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.95,0:04:28.95,DCEpTitle,EPTITLE,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(396,1)}The Romance Novel with the \NUnexpected Conclusion\N(Part One)
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.91,0:04:27.61,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,The Romance Novel with the \NUnexpected Conclusion, Part One!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.72,0:04:39.74,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Wow.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.74,0:04:41.98,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,This hotel has fifty floors.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.98,0:04:45.43,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,It's still shorter than my family's\NBell Tree Tower, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.92,0:04:47.16,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Of course it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.16,0:04:49.43,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,That's the tallest building in Japan.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.01,0:04:55.20,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,I'm planning on moving soon anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.20,0:04:56.77,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,You are?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.95,0:05:13.99,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,Who was that group of weird old men?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.99,0:05:19.32,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,Apparently they're waiting for manuscripts \Nfrom a popular author living in this hotel.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.32,0:05:21.17,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,I think his name was...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.17,0:05:22.67,DCMain,HIURA,0000,0000,0000,,Hiura Keigo.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.99,0:05:27.76,DCMain,HIURA,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}I'm what they call a romance novel author.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.01,0:05:27.76,Author,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(272,1)}Hiura Keigo (48)\NAuthor
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.76,0:05:29.18,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.18,0:05:32.17,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Um, I read your books.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.17,0:05:35.14,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Right now I'm really into "The \NPhone, the Ocean, and I."
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.14,0:05:37.42,DCMain,HIURA,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.42,0:05:38.66,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Not at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.66,0:05:41.02,DCMain,HIURA,0000,0000,0000,,You can put those anywhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.02,0:05:42.51,DCMain,MAN,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.51,0:05:44.37,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Excuse us.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.37,0:05:45.28,DCMain,HIURA,0000,0000,0000,,Sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.92,0:05:47.76,DCMain,HIURA,0000,0000,0000,,How about you guys?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.77,0:05:50.06,DCMain,HIURA,0000,0000,0000,,Why don't you join me in my room for lunch?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.06,0:05:51.47,DCMain,HIURA,0000,0000,0000,,Aren't you hungry?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.47,0:05:52.87,DCMain,EDITOR A,0000,0000,0000,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.87,0:05:54.82,DCMain,EDITOR B,0000,0000,0000,,We came for the manuscripts.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.82,0:05:56.66,DCMain,EDITOR C,0000,0000,0000,,The deadline is coming up.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.11,0:06:00.00,DCMain,HIRU,0000,0000,0000,,Don't be so rigid.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.00,0:06:01.97,DCMain,HIRU,0000,0000,0000,,I ordered too much food.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.97,0:06:04.17,DCMain,HIRU,0000,0000,0000,,I can't eat all of this myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.49,0:06:06.67,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe I'll get his autograph later.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.11,0:06:11.61,DCMain,EDITOR A,0000,0000,0000,,You really did order a lot of food.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.61,0:06:16.60,DCMain,EDITOR C,0000,0000,0000,,No wonder so many people were \Ncoming in and out of your room.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.60,0:06:20.60,DCMain,EDITOR B,0000,0000,0000,,I hadn't eaten lunch yet, so this is perfect.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.98,0:06:23.74,DCMain,HIURA,0000,0000,0000,,Eat as much as you'd like.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.41,0:06:25.74,DCMain,WOMAN,0000,0000,0000,,Room service.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.74,0:06:27.32,DCMain,WOMAN,0000,0000,0000,,I brought your wine.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.32,0:06:29.61,DCMain,HIURA,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, it's here.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.82,0:06:32.10,DCMain,WOMAN,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you for waiting.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.10,0:06:33.62,DCMain,HIURA,0000,0000,0000,,This is it.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.01,0:06:35.25,DCMain,HIURA,0000,0000,0000,,I've been waiting for this.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.25,0:06:37.24,DCMain,EDITOR A,0000,0000,0000,,S-Sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.24,0:06:38.83,DCMain,EDITOR A,0000,0000,0000,,Surely you don't intend to drink...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.83,0:06:40.79,DCMain,HIURA,0000,0000,0000,,Could you pour it into a decanter over there?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.79,0:06:43.27,DCMain,WOMAN,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, of course, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.52,0:06:45.80,DCMain,EDITOR A,0000,0000,0000,,S-Sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.43,0:06:51.56,DCMain,HIURA,0000,0000,0000,,I'd like to thank you for \Neverything you do for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.56,0:06:53.99,DCMain,HIURA,0000,0000,0000,,Don't hold back. Eat up.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.99,0:06:54.52,DCMain,EDITOR A,0000,0000,0000,,Okay...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.52,0:06:55.60,DCMain,EDITOR B,0000,0000,0000,,O-Okay...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.60,0:07:01.98,DCMain,HIURA,0000,0000,0000,,I'm thinking of finishing the manuscript \Nof whoever eats the most food first.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.20,0:07:03.82,DCMain,EDITOR A,0000,0000,0000,,B-But...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.82,0:07:05.28,DCMain,EDITOR C,0000,0000,0000,,How much we eat?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.28,0:07:06.48,DCMain,EDITOR B,0000,0000,0000,,How will you measure that?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.89,0:07:10.49,DCMain,HIURA,0000,0000,0000,,We'll measure your weight \Nbefore and after you eat.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.05,0:07:12.84,DCMain,HIURA,0000,0000,0000,,I have a scale.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.81,0:07:15.25,DCMain,MAN,0000,0000,0000,,I'm from Beika Sushi!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.25,0:07:16.52,DCMain,HIURA,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, it's here.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.52,0:07:18.68,DCMain,EDITOR B,0000,0000,0000,,Th-There's more?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.68,0:07:19.37,DCMain,HIURA,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.37,0:07:22.92,DCMain,HIURA,0000,0000,0000,,I have pizza, Chinese, \Nand donuts coming later.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.92,0:07:24.23,DCMain,HIURA,0000,0000,0000,,I'm counting on you boys.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.23,0:07:25.46,DCMain,ALL,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.46,0:07:27.80,DCMain,HIURA,0000,0000,0000,,While you're eating,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.81,0:07:31.38,DCMain,HIURA,0000,0000,0000,,I'll take a bath and come up with ideas.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.88,0:07:34.76,DCMain,HIURA,0000,0000,0000,,Keep a close eye on me...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.27,0:07:40.97,DCMain,HIURA,0000,0000,0000,,so I can't sneak out of this \Nroom to commit any mischief.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.09,0:07:45.56,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,What a wonderful view.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.45,0:07:49.99,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,I think I can see the curvature of the Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.99,0:07:52.67,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,This is the 30th floor...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.35,0:08:05.96,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,Conan-kun.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.48,0:08:08.34,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,That's the bedroom.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.34,0:08:11.11,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,It's kind of a mess, so don't go in there.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.11,0:08:12.30,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.30,0:08:17.35,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,If you want to see my dirty underwear, \Nyou're welcome to go in there.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.35,0:08:19.39,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,I think I'll pass...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.39,0:08:25.44,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, why don't we order something \Nfrom room service like that author?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.44,0:08:27.14,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,Great idea.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.14,0:08:29.94,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,I was just starting to get hungry.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.69,0:08:35.12,DCMain,HIURA,0000,0000,0000,,As promised, I'll finish the manuscripts \Nof whoever ate the most first.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.12,0:08:36.41,DCMain,HIURA,0000,0000,0000,,You just wait.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.41,0:08:38.04,DCMain,EDITOR A,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.18,0:08:43.73,DCMain,EDITOR C,0000,0000,0000,,I heard he was unusual...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.73,0:08:45.25,DCMain,EDITOR A,0000,0000,0000,,But I didn't know it was that bad.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.25,0:08:47.71,DCMain,EDITOR B,0000,0000,0000,,He had been down on his luck for a while,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.71,0:08:51.17,DCMain,EDITOR B,0000,0000,0000,,but recently he's been as \Npopular as he used to be.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.17,0:08:55.88,DCMain,EDITOR C,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't that thanks to the female \Nassistant he hired last year?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.88,0:08:56.72,DCMain,EDITOR A,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.56,0:08:59.03,DCMain,EDITOR A,0000,0000,0000,,Minazuki Chiaki.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.03,0:09:02.72,DCMain,EDITOR B,0000,0000,0000,,She got a room just below \NHiura-sensei's today, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.38,0:09:05.99,DCMain,EDITOR A,0000,0000,0000,,I haven't seen her, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.99,0:09:08.48,DCMain,EDITOR B,0000,0000,0000,,It's probably tough for her to \Ncome up while we're all here.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.48,0:09:12.09,DCMain,EDITOR B,0000,0000,0000,,A weekly magazine just wrote an \Narticle saying they might be lovers.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.09,0:09:16.17,DCMain,EDITOR C,0000,0000,0000,,Come to think of it, my department \Nreceived a threatening fax.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.17,0:09:19.91,DCMain,EDITOR C,0000,0000,0000,,It said to get his new \Nassistant away from him.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.25,0:09:22.83,DCMain,EDITOR B,0000,0000,0000,,We got that, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.83,0:09:26.45,DCMain,EDITOR C,0000,0000,0000,,He used to be a handsome author.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.45,0:09:29.33,DCMain,EDITOR C,0000,0000,0000,,I guess his female fans \Nare still in good health.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.04,0:09:33.98,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Kyogoku-san is so cute.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.98,0:09:35.15,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't he?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.15,0:09:38.09,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,I can't imagine a karate master saying that.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.09,0:09:39.16,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,If he likes ramen so much...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.16,0:09:42.33,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Talking about relationships at \Nan all girls afternoon tea party.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.33,0:09:44.72,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not sure I should be here.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.03,0:09:47.87,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,Don't you have any stories, Conan-kun?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.87,0:09:48.60,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.60,0:09:53.48,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe one about a girl you \Nonce met who you can't forget?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.48,0:09:55.90,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,N-Not really...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.85,0:10:02.96,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,I bet this kid is totally into Ayumi-chan.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.96,0:10:03.70,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.70,0:10:04.82,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,No way.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.82,0:10:06.73,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,I thought he liked Ai-chan.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.73,0:10:07.41,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.41,0:10:08.74,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,Her?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.74,0:10:09.21,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.70,0:10:11.99,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,Which girl do you like?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.99,0:10:13.34,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Wh-Which girl?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.91,0:10:16.39,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,We won't tell anyone, so tell us.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.39,0:10:18.71,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,I'm curious.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.71,0:10:21.14,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,It's you.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.06,0:10:23.93,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,It's already 6 o'clock.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.30,0:10:25.46,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, no.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.46,0:10:27.77,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,I need to get home and start making dinner.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.10,0:10:31.27,DCItalic,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,You got off lucky this time, kid.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.94,0:10:33.41,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,See you later.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.41,0:10:35.00,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks for today.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.00,0:10:35.71,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,Sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.71,0:10:37.53,DCMain,MAN,0000,0000,0000,,H-Hey! Ma'am?!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.96,0:10:40.85,DCMain,MAN,0000,0000,0000,,Ma'am, are you all right?! Ma'am!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.85,0:10:43.53,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,The clear resounding sound of this voice...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.49,0:10:45.81,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,He's downstairs!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.81,0:10:47.56,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.56,0:10:49.41,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,Wait, Ran!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.34,0:11:08.93,DCMain,MAN,0000,0000,0000,,Ma'am! Ma'am!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.26,0:11:11.44,DCMain,MAN,0000,0000,0000,,Are you all right, Minazuki-sama?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.68,0:11:12.95,DCMain,MAN,0000,0000,0000,,Minazuki-sama!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.22,0:11:17.27,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,The funicular marks on her neck suggest \Nshe was strangled by some kind of rope.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.27,0:11:21.95,DCItalic,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,She has scratches on her neck from \Nstruggling while being strangled.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.95,0:11:23.40,DCItalic,BOTH,0000,0000,0000,,She was strangled to death.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.40,0:11:25.45,DCMain,MAN,0000,0000,0000,,Wh-Who are you two?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.81,0:11:29.00,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Her jaw is starting to stiffen.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.62,0:11:32.69,DCItalic,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,It's been two or three hours since she died.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.69,0:11:34.13,DCMain,HIURA,0000,0000,0000,,Minazuki-kun!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.02,0:11:36.54,DCMain,HIURA,0000,0000,0000,,What's wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.02,0:11:38.46,DCMain,HIURA,0000,0000,0000,,What happened?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.46,0:11:39.96,DCMain,EDITOR C,0000,0000,0000,,Sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.40,0:11:42.12,DCMain,EDITOR C,0000,0000,0000,,There you are.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.12,0:11:45.18,DCMain,EDITOR C,0000,0000,0000,,You said you were just going \Nout to get some cigarettes.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.52,0:11:49.70,DCMain,HIURA,0000,0000,0000,,Minazuki-kun was collapsed \Nin the doorway of her room...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.70,0:11:50.54,DCMain,EDITOR C,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.54,0:11:53.30,DCMain,EDITOR C,0000,0000,0000,,You mean your assistant?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.18,0:11:55.90,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,She was killed.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.87,0:11:59.15,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,Someone strangled her to death.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.40,0:12:00.25,DCMain,BOTH,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.25,0:12:02.68,DCMain,HIURA,0000,0000,0000,,B-But why?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.68,0:12:05.59,DCMain,EDITOR C,0000,0000,0000,,M-Maybe it has something\Nto do with that fax.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.59,0:12:05.91,DCMain,HIURA,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.89,0:12:10.57,DCMain,EDITOR C,0000,0000,0000,,This morning, my department received a fax.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.58,0:12:13.87,Fax,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,If you don't fire the \Nassistant, you'll regret it.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.57,0:12:13.87,DCMain,EDITOR C,0000,0000,0000,,It said we'd regret it if we \Ndidn't fire his assistant.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.87,0:12:16.45,DCMain,HIURA,0000,0000,0000,,Why didn't you tell me about that?!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.66,0:12:20.24,DCMain,HIURA,0000,0000,0000,,You had plenty of opportunities to tell me!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.24,0:12:27.84,DCMain,HIURA,0000,0000,0000,,A-Are you saying I was working on a romance \Nnovel while this was happening to her?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.94,0:12:30.43,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Hmm?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.13,0:12:32.43,DCItalic,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.08,0:12:35.76,DCItalic,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,The culprit...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.76,0:12:36.94,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,...is this guy.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.76,0:12:49.95,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Champagne, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.28,0:12:54.56,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,When you came to deliver the \Nchampagne that was ordered,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.56,0:12:56.62,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,you discovered the body?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.62,0:12:57.96,DCMain,MAN,0000,0000,0000,,Y-Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.64,0:13:02.10,DCMain,MAN,0000,0000,0000,,I was told to bring it at exactly 6 PM.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.10,0:13:05.96,DCMain,MAN,0000,0000,0000,,The key card was stuck in the \Ndoor and it was slightly ajar.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.96,0:13:07.47,DCMain,MAN,0000,0000,0000,,I wondered what had happened, \Nso I opened the door.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.02,0:13:10.35,DCMain,MAN,0000,0000,0000,,I found her on the floor.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.33,0:13:12.73,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Do we know who the victim is?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.73,0:13:13.35,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.57,0:13:14.52,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Her name is...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.52,0:13:16.43,DCMain,HIURA,0000,0000,0000,,Minazuki Chiaki.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.43,0:13:19.11,DCMain,HIURA,0000,0000,0000,,She was my talented assistant.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.11,0:13:21.78,DCMain,HIURA,0000,0000,0000,,I think she was turning thirty this year.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.11,0:13:24.07,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Um, who are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.07,0:13:26.32,DCMain,HIURA,0000,0000,0000,,I'm the author Hiura Keigo.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.32,0:13:29.41,DCMain,HIURA,0000,0000,0000,,I'm the one who ordered the champagne.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.41,0:13:31.79,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Really? You ordered the champagne?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.15,0:13:32.79,DCMain,HIURA,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.56,0:13:38.11,DCMain,HIURA,0000,0000,0000,,I'm occupying the room \Ndirectly above this one.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.11,0:13:40.99,DCMain,HIURA,0000,0000,0000,,I was writing, but I thought I \Nwould be finished around 6 o'clock.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.99,0:13:43.80,DCMain,HIURA,0000,0000,0000,,I thought we could share a celebratory drink.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.48,0:13:49.74,DCMain,HIURA,0000,0000,0000,,I never imagined this would happen \Nto her while I was writing.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.74,0:13:53.31,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Did you come here because \Nyou finished writing?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.31,0:13:56.96,DCMain,HIURA,0000,0000,0000,,No, I was having trouble \Nfinishing the last pages.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.96,0:13:58.55,DCMain,HIURA,0000,0000,0000,,About thirty minutes ago,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.55,0:14:03.32,DCMain,HIURA,0000,0000,0000,,I went out to buy cigarettes for a change \Nof pace and wander around while thinking.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.58,0:14:09.32,DCMain,HIURA,0000,0000,0000,,I bought cigarettes from the vending \Nmachines in the elevator hall two floors down.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.97,0:14:14.19,DCMain,HIURA,0000,0000,0000,,While climbing the stairs, I heard this\Nbellboy scream and came running.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.07,0:14:19.62,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,You were just wandering around, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.07,0:14:24.35,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,How did you know she was killed \Nwhile you were working on your book?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.35,0:14:25.00,DCMain,HIURA,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.35,0:14:28.51,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,She may have been killed just now.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.40,0:14:35.79,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,Her jaw was beginning to stiffen \Nwhen her body was discovered.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.79,0:14:39.27,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,I think it's been about two or \Nthree hours since her death.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.78,0:14:43.73,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,If you knew that without \Neven touching her body,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.73,0:14:48.92,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,maybe you should switch to \Nbeing a mystery author instead?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.48,0:14:51.06,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Well?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.06,0:14:53.27,DCMain,HIURA,0000,0000,0000,,Sh-She didn't come to my room.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.27,0:15:01.02,DCMain,HIURA,0000,0000,0000,,She was supposed to bring documents \Nto my room a couple hours ago,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.02,0:15:02.50,DCMain,HIURA,0000,0000,0000,,but she never came.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.50,0:15:08.35,DCMain,HIURA,0000,0000,0000,,When I saw her body, I assumed she \Ncouldn't come because she'd been killed.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.96,0:15:15.20,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,So was she actually killed \Ntwo or three hours ago?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.75,0:15:16.56,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.99,0:15:18.41,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,According to the coroner,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.41,0:15:22.26,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,her estimated time of death is two and a \Nhalf hours before her body was discovered.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.26,0:15:25.57,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,She was strangled around 3:30 PM.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.07,0:15:30.98,DCMain,HIURA,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't that around the time you \Nboys were eating in my room?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.98,0:15:31.76,DCMain,EDITOR C,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.76,0:15:33.46,DCMain,EDITOR C,0000,0000,0000,,We started just after 3 o'clock.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.46,0:15:34.57,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Who are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.87,0:15:39.95,DCMain,EDITOR C,0000,0000,0000,,I'm Hiura-sensei's editor \Nat Nichiuri Publishing.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.95,0:15:43.65,DCMain,EDITOR C,0000,0000,0000,,He ordered too much food,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.66,0:15:48.59,DCMain,EDITOR C,0000,0000,0000,,so we were eating in his\Nroom with two other editors.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.59,0:15:52.09,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Y-You were working on three manuscripts?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.09,0:15:53.03,DCMain,HIURA,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.03,0:15:55.58,DCMain,HIURA,0000,0000,0000,,Their deadlines conflicted.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.58,0:16:00.60,DCMain,HIURA,0000,0000,0000,,I decided to finish the manuscripts of \Nthe editors who ate the most food first.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.96,0:16:04.08,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Did Hiura-san eat with you?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.08,0:16:04.93,DCMain,EDITOR C,0000,0000,0000,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.93,0:16:10.07,DCMain,EDITOR C,0000,0000,0000,,While we were eating, he went to \Ntake a bath so he could think.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.07,0:16:11.11,DCMain,HIURA,0000,0000,0000,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.40,0:16:14.28,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Couldn't you have snuck \Nout of the room then?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.74,0:16:16.25,DCMain,EDITOR C,0000,0000,0000,,That's not possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.25,0:16:20.29,DCMain,EDITOR C,0000,0000,0000,,Several food deliveries arrived afterwards,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.29,0:16:25.29,DCMain,EDITOR C,0000,0000,0000,,but we could clearly see the entryway from \Nthe living room where we were eating.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.56,0:16:28.38,DCMain,EDITOR C,0000,0000,0000,,We paid for the food,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.38,0:16:32.62,DCMain,EDITOR C,0000,0000,0000,,so I don't think Hiura-sensei even \Napproached the doorway while we were eating.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.62,0:16:35.30,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,How long were you eating?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.61,0:16:37.73,DCMain,EDITOR C,0000,0000,0000,,Until around 4:30.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.73,0:16:40.74,DCMain,EDITOR C,0000,0000,0000,,When we finished eating and left his room,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.74,0:16:46.16,DCMain,EDITOR C,0000,0000,0000,,we could see the door to his room \Nwhile waiting for the elevators.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.16,0:16:51.82,DCMain,EDITOR C,0000,0000,0000,,He only left the room to give his \Nfinished manuscript to an editor.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.82,0:16:54.79,DCMain,EDITOR C,0000,0000,0000,,He returned to his room \Nimmediately afterwards.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.79,0:16:57.58,DCMain,EDITOR C,0000,0000,0000,,I don't think he had a chance to sneak out.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.58,0:17:01.53,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Does that mean you finished three \Nmanuscripts in a short amount of time?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.53,0:17:02.58,DCMain,HIURA,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.58,0:17:05.33,DCMain,HIURA,0000,0000,0000,,I had nearly finished all three of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.89,0:17:07.61,DCMain,HIURA,0000,0000,0000,,But as I said earlier,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.61,0:17:14.09,DCMain,HIURA,0000,0000,0000,,I was stuck on the last scene of "The Phone,\Nthe Ocean, and I" which he works on.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.52,0:17:19.50,DCMain,HIURA,0000,0000,0000,,After 5:30, I printed out everything \Nexcept the final pages to give to him,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.50,0:17:22.52,DCMain,HIURA,0000,0000,0000,,and went to buy cigarettes.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.52,0:17:25.74,DCMain,HIURA,0000,0000,0000,,I thought he could read it while he waited.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.74,0:17:27.34,DCMain,HIURA,0000,0000,0000,,Right?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.34,0:17:28.10,DCMain,EDITOR C,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.50,0:17:31.37,DCMain,EDITOR C,0000,0000,0000,,He headed towards the stairs \Nwith his wallet in his hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.37,0:17:33.76,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Not the elevators?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.76,0:17:35.98,DCMain,HIURA,0000,0000,0000,,The stairs do more to inspire me.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.98,0:17:37.61,DCMain,HIURA,0000,0000,0000,,It's good exercise, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.06,0:17:44.35,DCMain,EDITOR C,0000,0000,0000,,While I was reading the manuscript, \NI heard the bellboy shouting.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.35,0:17:49.13,DCMain,EDITOR C,0000,0000,0000,,Hiura-sensei called to tell me \Nsomething had happened downstairs.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.35,0:17:53.80,DCMain,EDITOR C,0000,0000,0000,,When I got here, you were all \Nstanding in front of the room.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.57,0:17:55.86,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.86,0:18:00.05,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Can you think of anyone who may have \Nborn a grudge against Minazuki-san?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.37,0:18:02.56,DCMain,HIURA,0000,0000,0000,,It's the threatening fax!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.90,0:18:06.25,DCMain,HIURA,0000,0000,0000,,The culprit must be whoever sent that!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.25,0:18:08.16,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,The threatening fax?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.16,0:18:11.06,DCMain,EDITOR C,0000,0000,0000,,It arrived this morning at \Nmy editorial department.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.51,0:18:15.81,DCMain,EDITOR C,0000,0000,0000,,It said, "If you don't fire the \Nassistant, you'll regret it."
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.81,0:18:20.99,DCMain,EDITOR C,0000,0000,0000,,We did check the sender, but \Nit was a convenience store.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.94,0:18:23.99,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Why was she being threatened, though?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.99,0:18:28.39,DCMain,HIURA,0000,0000,0000,,It's because a weekly magazine printed \Npictures of us walking around town together,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.39,0:18:30.75,DCMain,HIURA,0000,0000,0000,,with the caption that we might be lovers!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.17,0:18:34.73,DCMain,HIURA,0000,0000,0000,,Because of it, my wife went \Nback to her parents' house.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.73,0:18:38.18,DCMain,EDITOR C,0000,0000,0000,,Nearly all his works are \Nabout pure and genuine love.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.18,0:18:41.06,DCMain,EDITOR C,0000,0000,0000,,He has many female fans\Nwho despise adultery.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.95,0:18:45.89,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,What was your relationship with \NMinazuki-san actually like?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.89,0:18:47.81,DCMain,HIURA,0000,0000,0000,,There was nothing between us!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.19,0:18:53.69,DCMain,HIURA,0000,0000,0000,,She was a great assistant\Nwith plenty of ideas.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.69,0:18:56.46,DCMain,HIURA,0000,0000,0000,,She worked so hard on "The \NPhone, the Ocean, and I."
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.47,0:19:01.47,DCMain,HIURA,0000,0000,0000,,You could practically call it her work.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.47,0:19:07.20,DCMain,HIURA,0000,0000,0000,,I was thinking of letting her become \Nan independent writer next year.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.43,0:19:10.25,DCMain,HIURA,0000,0000,0000,,But why?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.36,0:19:13.51,DCMain,HIURA,0000,0000,0000,,Why her?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.58,0:20:43.47,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Let the police handle this.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.47,0:20:46.39,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Conan-kun and Sera-san, you can leave now.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.92,0:20:51.64,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,We might question some witnesses later.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.64,0:20:53.03,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.39,0:20:56.92,DCMain,MAN,0000,0000,0000,,What happened?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.92,0:20:57.86,DCMain,MAN,0000,0000,0000,,There was a murder?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.86,0:20:58.59,DCMain,MAN,0000,0000,0000,,A murder?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.59,0:20:59.47,DCMain,MAN,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.47,0:21:01.73,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Whoa. Look at this crowd.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.73,0:21:03.98,DCItalic,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,When did they get here?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.43,0:21:17.65,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Excuse me. Let me through, please.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.85,0:21:23.21,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Where is she?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.21,0:21:24.49,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Where did she go?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.95,0:21:32.05,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Why are you scowling like that, Conan-kun?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.05,0:21:34.49,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Did you see a girl?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.49,0:21:36.73,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,What? A girl?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.73,0:21:38.35,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Sonoko, did you see one?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.35,0:21:39.30,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.30,0:21:41.94,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,She was here in this crowd.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.53,0:21:46.57,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,A middle school aged girl \Nwho looks just like Sera!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.99,0:21:49.68,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,A middle school student \Nwho looks like Sera-san?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.68,0:21:53.08,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,But she said she doesn't have a sister.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.39,0:21:55.35,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe you were mistaken.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.59,0:22:02.00,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,It wasn't a mistake. She was there.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.60,0:22:06.38,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,There was a picture of a girl who \Nlooks like Sera on her phone, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:08.32,0:22:09.92,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Who is she?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:20.99,0:22:22.36,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,What? No way!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:22.36,0:22:25.11,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,The author Hiura-san is the suspect?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:25.11,0:22:26.92,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,I-Is it true?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:26.92,0:22:29.27,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, probably.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:29.27,0:22:33.74,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,But I thought he had an alibi.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:34.05,0:22:38.69,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,He was in his room with his \Neditors watching over him.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:38.69,0:22:39.54,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:39.54,0:22:41.66,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,In order to break his alibi down,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:41.66,0:22:46.59,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,I need to come up with a way to get \Ninto the victim's room one floor below.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:47.13,0:22:49.92,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,We're thirty floors up.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:49.92,0:22:53.76,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,Using a rope to climb down from \Nthe balcony would be pretty scary.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:54.36,0:22:58.52,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,If the editors could see the entryway from \Nwhere they were eating in the living room,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:58.51,0:23:01.45,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,then they must have been able \Nto see the balcony, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:05.30,0:23:06.82,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,Right, Conan-kun?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:06.82,0:23:08.22,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,H-Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:09.57,0:23:11.41,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,Don't you agree?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:11.66,0:23:13.41,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Y-Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:18.16,0:23:19.55,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, no!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:19.55,0:23:21.53,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,I forgot to make dinner!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:21.53,0:23:23.21,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,I'd better call my dad!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:23.21,0:23:26.58,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,Uh, oh. Mouri-san must be fuming.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:26.58,0:23:29.22,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,He's pretty scary when he's upset over food.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:29.70,0:23:31.67,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Dad?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:32.81,0:23:34.08,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:34.08,0:23:37.22,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,I was visiting Sera-san's place, \Nand something happened...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:38.97,0:23:40.23,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not lying.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:44.90,0:23:47.90,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,The caps for the shampoo and \Nconditioner are missing?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:44.90,0:24:08.92,DCEpPreview,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,Episode Preview
Dialogue: 0,0:23:48.19,0:23:51.09,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,We came in through the main entrance.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:51.09,0:23:54.03,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Did you knock over the table, too?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:54.34,0:23:57.85,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,There were lots of people \Nbringing delivery food, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:57.85,0:23:59.04,DCMain,EDITOR,0000,0000,0000,,Y-Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:59.40,0:24:05.79,DCMain,HIURA,0000,0000,0000,,How did I move the body from \Nthis room to the one below?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:05.79,0:24:08.92,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,That's right. That was his goal.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:08.92,0:24:14.93,DCNextEp,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,The Romance Novel with the \NUnexpected Conclusion\N(Part Two)
Dialogue: 0,0:24:09.57,0:24:14.54,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,The next episode is "The Romance Novel\Nwith the Unexpected Conclusion, Part Two!"
Dialogue: 0,0:24:29.94,0:24:34.95,Letter,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,An Old Letter
Dialogue: 0,0:24:30.47,0:24:32.66,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,Next Conan's hint!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:32.66,0:24:34.95,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,An old letter!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:34.95,0:24:40.34,Don'tMiss,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,Don't miss the next episode.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:35.20,0:24:37.04,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Does Sera-san really bother you that much?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:37.04,0:24:38.39,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}There you go again, you precocious brat.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:38.39,0:24:39.69,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}It's not like that.
